What do you get when take the Hellfire Cannon and bind the most powerful demons of the Pestilent God? The Filth Maw!
A vile, disease ridden contraption where the crew even fear to get too close.

This kit includes everything you need to build the Filth Maw Hellfire Cannon.
- Filth Maw
- 3 crew

The model has been made to go on a 100x150mm base, crew on 25mm and these bases have been included.

There are additional accessory pieces:
- x2 pestilent pools for decorating the base
- x1 flaming skull pile
- x11 potion bottles, some plain, others with vile evil dwarf symbols and empty versions
- x1 steps for an alternate pose for a crew to look like they are
- x1 distill

Files come supported and unsupported.
There is also a helpful PDF with some useful tips on print and build.
Happy printing!

Pictures of models are test prints.

Sorcerers are the undisputed leaders of evil dwarfs well versed in the darkest magics of their patron Bull God.
Some are specialised in the art of Fireborn summoning, so much so they enslave them to other purposes only limited by their imagination.

The palanquin has a 26mm square impression so you can place models with a 25mm base inside of it.
Included in this file to optionally place on top:
- 1 Sorcerer designed to be on a 25mm square base.
- 1 Sacrificial brazier with a 26mm square base already incorporated so it lays flush with the palanquin.

This model is designed as a unit filler for your evil dwarf armies. It is pictured here on a 40mm base.

This file contains:
- 1 Fireborn Sorcerer
- 1 Brazier
- 1 Palanquin with enslaved Fireborn
- 1 Palanquin by itself if you want to model other bearers with it or just as a cool base accessory.

Files come pre-supported and unsupported.

Happy printing!

Pictures of models are test prints and shown with Fireborn unit for scale.

Mixing the darkest of magics with the fires of the Bull God, the Fire Elemental Demons are born for destruction and little else!

When fully assembled these Fire Elemental Demons stand about 60mm tall. They are designed to go on 40mm bases.
This is a multipart kit for an incredible amount of variety to your units. It contains:
- 4 torsos
- 6 heads plus a unit champion (has a big hat/crown and chain beard)
- 2 upper bodies, these can be mirrored
- 3 lower bodies, these can be mirrored
- 6 weapons, these can be mirrored and used for either hand

Files come pre-supported and unsupported.

Happy printing!

ASSEMBLY
- Good to print a variety of parts, most things should dry fit to a point so you can get the poses just right.
- I recommend glueing together one Fire Demon at a time. This way you can plan the next Fire Demon so they rank up nicely (I did my best however to give the right balance between pose and variety).

Pictures of models are test prints.

The Evil Dwarfs are friends with angry folk. The demonic bulls give you two different options. A red winged bull and a larger angrier bull that has wings aflame.

These files come supported and unsupported.

Both red and flame bull are INCLUDED in this download.

They both also come with two different flight stands (varying height) and stls versions that have holes to fit the flight stands in. The holes have been made to allow the flight stands to either go in directly or on an angle.

Note the wings are in one pose, however my recommendation is that you bend and tape (use clear tape) to the desired angle before curing. Use some hot water to further soften the wings for bending. Then dry and apply the tape. With the tape secured you an cure the model and the wings will stay at their taped shape :)

The rock base has been designed for the flaming bull. There are two versions, one with impressions to stick the bull on and one to allow you to stick him anywhere. It also includes sizes for 40x20mm bases and 25mm round bases.

Enjoy!
